#compdef alembic
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# sqlalchemy/alembic alembic/config.py + alembic/command.py
# (Python **argparse**; corpus's first documented Python
# argparse CLI):
#   alembic/config.py line 3 (`from argparse import
#     ArgumentParser`)
#   alembic/config.py lines 690-952 (CommandLine class
#     with `_generate_args` and **introspection-driven
#     subcommand registration** via `register_command`)
#   alembic/config.py lines 696-836 (_KWARGS_OPTS dict —
#     metadata for kwargs auto-detected from function
#     signatures: long/short flag + action/type/help)
#   alembic/config.py lines 837-845 (_POSITIONAL_OPTS
#     dict — metadata for positionals; `revisions` uses
#     `nargs="+"`)
#   alembic/config.py lines 846-848 (_POSITIONAL_TRANSLATIONS
#     — per-command positional rename: stamp's `revision`
#     becomes `revisions`)
#   alembic/config.py lines 851-907 (_generate_args fn:
#     6 global flags + auto-iterates `dir(command)` and
#     `register_command(fn)` for every public function)
#   alembic/config.py lines 909-934 (register_command:
#     inspects function via `inspect.getfullargspec`,
#     uses docstring first line(s) as help, adds kwargs
#     via _KWARGS_OPTS lookup, positionals via
#     _POSITIONAL_OPTS lookup)
#   alembic/command.py lines 25-832 (15 public function
#     subcommands: list_templates / init / revision /
#     check / merge / upgrade / downgrade / show /
#     history / heads / branches / current / stamp /
#     edit / ensure_version)
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# alembic is the **SQLAlchemy database migration tool**
# — the de-facto Python ORM migration system for
# SQLAlchemy-based projects.  Used by FastAPI / Flask /
# Django (in async mode) / Litestar projects.  Pivots
# from Click (R266 uvicorn) into the **argparse +
# introspection** subspace of the Python CLI taxonomy.
# Sister to Django's `manage.py` migrate / Rails'
# `db:migrate` / Knex.js migrations.
#
# Critical extraction note: alembic uses **Python
# argparse** library at `from argparse import
# ArgumentParser` — corpus's **first documented Python
# argparse CLI**.  Completes the **3-way Python CLI
# library taxonomy** (now COMPLETE): (a) **argparse**
# (R267 alembic — Python stdlib), (b) **Click** (R266
# uvicorn — decorator-based), (c) **Typer** (modern;
# type-hint-driven; deferred).  argparse is the stdlib
# choice; built-in to every Python install; declarative
# but verbose compared to Click; supports subcommands
# via `parser.add_subparsers()` + `subparser.add_parser
# (name, ...)`.  Distinct from Click's decorator stack
# in style — argparse builds the parser tree imperatively.
#
# Critical extraction note: alembic uses **INTROSPECTION-
# DRIVEN SUBCOMMAND REGISTRATION** at config.py:893-905
# — iterates `dir(command)` and registers every PUBLIC
# function in `alembic.command` as a subcommand
# automatically via `register_command(fn)`.  The
# subcommand NAME matches `fn.__name__`; the HELP text
# is read from `fn.__doc__` (first contiguous block);
# the ARGS are extracted from `inspect.getfullargspec(fn)`.
# Positional args (no default) become argparse
# positionals; kwargs (with defaults) become argparse
# options.  Documents the **introspection-driven CLI
# pattern** — corpus's first.  Distinct from clap derive's
# struct-attribute approach and from Click's decorator
# stack.  Powerful because adding a new command to
# `alembic/command.py` AUTO-REGISTERS it in the CLI
# without modifying the CLI code.  But adds **runtime
# overhead** (inspection at startup) and reduces clarity
# (CLI surface implicit in function signatures).
# Documents the **convention-over-configuration extreme**
# in Python CLI design.
#
# Critical extraction note: alembic uses **`_KWARGS_OPTS`
# + `_POSITIONAL_OPTS` PER-ARG METADATA DICTS** at
# config.py:696-848 — when registering a command,
# argparse needs to know each arg's type, action, help
# text, short/long flag names.  alembic stores these in
# 2 class-level dicts keyed by ARG NAME (not function
# name) — so the SAME arg `verbose` always gets `-v/
# --verbose action=store_true help="Use more verbose
# output"` regardless of which subcommand has it.
# Documents the **shared-arg-metadata-by-name pattern**
# — DRY for CLIs where the same arg name appears in
# multiple subcommands.  18 kwargs documented in
# _KWARGS_OPTS (template / message / sql / tag / head /
# splice / depends_on / rev_id / version_path /
# branch_label / verbose / resolve_dependencies /
# autogenerate / rev_range / indicate_current / purge /
# package / check_heads).  3 positionals documented in
# _POSITIONAL_OPTS (directory / revision / revisions
# where `revisions` uses `nargs="+"` for "one or more").
#
# Critical extraction note: alembic uses
# **`_POSITIONAL_TRANSLATIONS = {command.stamp: {"revision":
# "revisions"}}`** at config.py:846-848 — a TRANSLATION
# DICT that renames the introspected positional arg
# from `revision` to `revisions` ONLY for the `stamp`
# subcommand (because `stamp` accepts multiple revisions
# but the function signature names it singular).
# Documents the **per-command positional-name override
# pattern** — when the function signature name differs
# from the desired CLI positional name (e.g. for
# pluralization, semantic clarity).  Corpus's **first
# documented introspection-override mechanism** in a CLI.
# Subtle but necessary when introspection meets
# semantic CLI design.
#
# Critical extraction note: alembic uses **`action=
# "version"`** at config.py:855 on `--version` — the
# argparse builtin `version` action automatically prints
# the version string (`"%%(prog)s %s" % __version__`)
# and exits 0.  No callback needed.  Documents the
# **argparse builtin `version` action** — Python stdlib
# argparse has a small set of builtin actions: store,
# store_const, store_true, store_false, append,
# append_const, count, help, version, extend (3.8+).
# Distinct from R266 uvicorn's Click `--version` (which
# requires explicit `callback=print_version,
# expose_value=False, is_eager=True`).  argparse's
# `version` is one line; Click's needs 3 attributes.
# Corpus's first documented argparse `action="version"`.
#
# Critical extraction note: alembic uses **`-c/--config
# action="append"`** at config.py:858-865 — the `--config`
# option can be specified MULTIPLE TIMES, with values
# accumulating into a list.  E.g. `alembic -c base.ini
# -c overlay.toml command` collects to `config =
# ['base.ini', 'overlay.toml']`.  Documents the
# **argparse `action="append"` pattern** — distinct
# from clap's `Vec<T>` (auto-multiple) and Click's
# `multiple=True`.  argparse's append is the explicit
# action.  Plus the help text describes the dual-config
# semantics: alembic.ini OR pyproject.toml OR BOTH.
# Useful for CLIs that need to layer multiple
# configuration sources.

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1

# 15 subcommands decoded source-direct from
# alembic/command.py public function list.  Each is
# auto-registered by `register_command(fn)` iterating
# `dir(command)`.
local -a subcommands=(
  'list_templates:list available templates for `init`'
  'init:initialize a new scripts directory (default template: generic)'
  'revision:create a new revision file'
  'check:check for unapplied changes (autogenerate diff)'
  'merge:merge two revisions together (creates a new revision)'
  'upgrade:upgrade to a later version'
  'downgrade:revert to a previous version'
  'show:show the revision(s) denoted by the given symbol'
  'history:list revision changesets prior to the current'
  'heads:show current available heads in the script directory'
  'branches:show current branch points'
  'current:display the current revision for a database'
  'stamp:stamp the revision table with the given revision; do not run any migrations'
  'edit:edit the revision script(s) using $EDITOR'
  'ensure_version:create the alembic version table if not present (without running any migrations)'
)

# Global flags decoded source-direct from
# _generate_args at config.py lines 854-892.
local -a global_flags=(
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help]'
  '--version[show version (argparse action="version" builtin)]'
  '*'{-c+,--config=}'[alternate config file (alembic.ini or pyproject.toml; env: ALEMBIC_CONFIG; append-action: may be specified twice)]:file:_files -g "*.(ini|toml)"'
  '(-n --name)'{-n+,--name=}'[name of section in .ini file (only applies to configparser; not toml)]:name:'
  '*-x+[additional arg consumed by custom env.py (e.g. -x setting1=value)]:setting:'
  '--raiseerr[raise a full stack trace on error]'
  '(-q --quiet)'{-q,--quiet}'[do not log to std output]'
)

# Common flag definitions reused across multiple
# subcommands via _KWARGS_OPTS.
local -a flag_sql=('--sql[do not emit SQL to database; dump to stdout/file (offline mode)]')
local -a flag_tag=('--tag=[arbitrary tag name (used by custom env.py scripts)]:tag:')
local -a flag_message=('(-m --message)'{-m+,--message=}'[message string]:message:')
local -a flag_verbose=('(-v --verbose)'{-v,--verbose}'[use more verbose output]')
local -a flag_head=('--head=[head revision or <branchname>@head to base new revision on]:head:')
local -a flag_branch_label=('--branch-label=[branch label to apply to new revision]:label:')
local -a flag_rev_id=('--rev-id=[hardcoded revision id instead of generating one]:id:')

_arguments -C \
  $global_flags \
  '1:subcommand:->subcmd' \
  '*::args:->args' && ret=0

case $state in
  subcmd)
    _describe -t subcommands 'alembic subcommand' subcommands && ret=0
    ;;
  args)
    case $words[1] in
      init)
        _arguments \
          '(-t --template)'{-t+,--template=}'[setup template (default: generic)]:template:(generic async multidb pyproject)' \
          '--package[write empty __init__.py files to environment and version locations]' \
          '1:directory (location of scripts directory):_files -/' && ret=0
        ;;
      revision)
        _arguments \
          $flag_message \
          '--autogenerate[populate revision script with candidate migration ops via model-vs-db comparison]' \
          $flag_sql \
          $flag_head \
          '--splice[allow a non-head revision as the head to splice onto]' \
          $flag_branch_label \
          '--version-path=[specific path from config for version file]:path:_files -/' \
          $flag_rev_id \
          '*--depends-on=[revision identifier(s) this revision should depend on]:rev:' && ret=0
        ;;
      check)
        _arguments && ret=0
        ;;
      merge)
        _arguments \
          $flag_message \
          $flag_branch_label \
          $flag_rev_id \
          '*:revision identifiers (one or more, or "heads" for all heads):' && ret=0
        ;;
      upgrade|downgrade)
        _arguments \
          $flag_sql \
          $flag_tag \
          '1:revision identifier:' && ret=0
        ;;
      show|edit)
        _arguments \
          '1:revision identifier:' && ret=0
        ;;
      history)
        _arguments \
          '(-r --rev-range)'{-r+,--rev-range=}'[revision range: [start]:[end]]:range:' \
          '(-i --indicate-current)'{-i,--indicate-current}'[indicate the current revision]' \
          $flag_verbose && ret=0
        ;;
      heads)
        _arguments \
          $flag_verbose \
          '--resolve-dependencies[treat dependency versions as down revisions]' && ret=0
        ;;
      branches|current)
        _arguments \
          $flag_verbose && ret=0
        ;;
      stamp)
        _arguments \
          $flag_sql \
          $flag_tag \
          '--purge[unconditionally erase the version table before stamping]' \
          '*:revision identifier(s) (nargs=+; "heads" for all heads):' && ret=0
        ;;
      ensure_version)
        _arguments $flag_sql && ret=0
        ;;
    esac
    ;;
esac

return ret
